# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# ScaleIn Storage Role Assignments - REMOVED FOR DEV ENVIRONMENT
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# In dev environment, ScaleIn uses the shared identity (same as ScaleOut).
# These role assignments have count=0 in dev because:
#   create_scalein_role_assignments = create_scalein_identity && !use_shared_identity
#
# Since use_shared_identity = true in dev:
#   create_scalein_role_assignments = false && !true = false && false = false
#
# The shared identity already has necessary permissions via ScaleOut assignments.
# Storage-scoped permissions are inherited.
#
# For test/prod with separate ScaleIn identity, these would need to be imported:
# - scalein_storage_blob[0]
# - scalein_storage_queue[0]
# - scalein_storage_table[0]
# - scalein_scaleout_table_reader[0]
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Role Assignments - ScaleIn identity conflict resolution
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# IMPORTANT: In dev environment, both ScaleOut and ScaleIn use the SAME shared
# identity (principal ID: 50f93b9e-62a8-4fbd-818e-107ba9a17142).
#
# This means the following role assignments would be DUPLICATES if created:
# - scalein_vm_contributor → CONFLICTS with scaleout_vm_contributor (same scope + principal)
# - scalein_reader → CONFLICTS with scaleout_reader (same scope + principal)
# - scalein_contributor → CONFLICTS with scaleout_contributor (same scope + principal)
#
# Azure RBAC does NOT allow duplicate role assignments (same principal + role + scope).
# The errors "RoleAssignmentExists" occur when Terraform tries to create these.
#
# Solution: These scalein assignments should have `count = 0` in dev because the
# shared identity already has these permissions via scaleout assignments.
# Only the storage-scoped assignments are unique to scalein (different scope).
#
# FIXED: Updated main.tf to set:
#   create_scalein_role_assignments = create_scalein_identity && !use_shared_identity
# This prevents duplicate role assignments when using shared identity.
#
# Result: In dev, scalein_vm_contributor, scalein_reader, and scalein_contributor
# have count=0, so we do NOT import them (they don't exist in Terraform state).
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

